title: The Intrigues at Versailles, or A Jilt in All Humours

items: Duke de Sanserre . Proud , and Hot-Spirited ; very Amorous , Jealous and Revengeful Mr. Betterton .
Guillamour . A young English Lord , a great Intreaguer . Mr. Verbruggen .
Count de Brissac . An Old Beau , Ridiculously Apish , and fond of young Company . Mr. Boen .
Count de Fiesque . Witty , Generous , and good Natur'd , but Amorous to a Fault . Mr. Hodson .
Count de Tonnere . Young and Extravaant , Intreagu'd with Lady Brissac , and Disguis'd in Womens Clothes , upon the account of a Duel . Mr. Bowman .
Sir Blunder Bosses . A dull sordid Brute , and Mongril whose Humour is , to call every Body by Clownish Names . Mr. Vnderhill .
Rambure . An Old Affected Fellow . Valett to Fiesque .
Dutch . de Sanserre Poetical , High-Spirited , and Wanton . Mrs. Bracegirdle .
Countess de Brissac . Young , Wild , and Extravagant . Mrs. Bowman .
Madam de Vandosme . A Right Jilt in all Humours . Mrs. Barry .
Daubray . A Retainer , and Spy to the Duke de Sanserre . Mrs. Willis .
La Busque . Confident to the Dutchess . Mrs. Lawson .
Grossiere ; Page to Sanserre . A Finical Jilt , Confident to Vandosme . Mrs. Leigh .
